The paper proposes a new method for online feature extraction and model learning for multi-way data using tensor analysis. This is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new method for online feature extraction and model learning, which is a core problem in machine learning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new method for learning from multi-way data, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new method for online feature extraction and model learning, which involves designing efficient algorithms for tensor analysis. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper evaluates the proposed method on structural health monitoring datasets, which suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision and pattern recognition sub-category.
